full_requirement_text: All trial personnel must receive role-specific GCP training prior to trial activities.
original_text:
Good Clinical Practice – Training & Records
All trial personnel must receive role-specific GCP training prior to trial activities. Training shall be documented, retained, and periodically evaluated for effectiveness.

| Training Aspect | Mandatory | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Role-specific GCP training | Yes | Before trial activities |
| Training documentation | Yes | Maintain records |
| Training effectiveness assessment | Yes | Periodic review |

full_requirement_text: All Serious Adverse Events (SAEs) must be reported immediately to the sponsor.
original_text:
Good Clinical Practice – Safety Reporting
All Serious Adverse Events (SAEs) must be reported immediately to the sponsor. Initial reports shall be followed by detailed written follow-up reports.

| Event Type | Initial Reporting | Follow-up Requirement |
| --- | --- | --- |
| SAE | Immediate (≤24 hrs) | Detailed written report |
| Critical AE | Immediate | As defined in protocol |

Protocol-defined critical adverse events must be reported irrespective of seriousness.

full_requirement_text: The Investigator must be qualified by education.
original_text:
Good Clinical Practice – Investigator Responsibilities
Section 1: Qualification
The Investigator must be qualified by education, training, and experience. Evidence of such qualification shall be maintained and made available for inspection.

| Requirement ID | Requirement Description |
| --- | --- |
| Q-1 | Qualification by education |
| Q-2 | Qualification by training |
| Q-3 | Qualification by experience |
| Q-4 | Documentation demonstrating qualification |

Section 2: Delegation of Duties
The Investigator must maintain a delegation log. Delegated personnel shall be appropriately qualified and trained for assigned duties.
